<p><big><font color="#008040"><b>Basic Physics</b></font></big></p>
<p>Consider the situation depicted in Fig. 2. The waveguide, a
slab of material of thickness <i >d</i> and
index of refraction <i >n</i><sub>1</sub>, is
sandwiched between two media, the cladding, of index of refraction <i>n</i><sub>2</sub>. The wavelengths of the
light in the two media are, respectively, <!-- MP EQ( --><script>
